ðŸ“„ Contract Management System (Frontend)

-A simple contract management web application built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
This project allows users to create contracts, track their lifecycle, view status updates in real time, and interact with a floating AI assistant on every page.


#Features

-Create contracts using predefined templates
-Live contract preview while filling details
-Contract lifecycle tracking: 
   -Created
   -Approved
   -Sent
   -Signed
   -Locked

-Dashboard with real-time phase counts
-Data stored using LocalStorage (no backend required)
-Floating AI Chatbot Assistant available on all pages
-Download contract as PDF after signing
-Clean and professional UI layout


#Application Flow (How it Works)

1.Login Page
  -User logs in (basic demo login).

2.Dashboard
  -Shows list of all contracts.
  -Displays contract phase summary cards (Created, Approved, Sent, Signed, Locked).
  -Counts update automatically when contract status changes.

3.Create Contract
  -Select a template (Employment, NDA, Lease, Service, Vendor).
  -Fill required details.
  -Live preview updates instantly.
  -Upload signature.
  -Save contract.

4.View Contract
  -See full contract preview.
  -Update contract status using timeline buttons.
  -Download PDF only after signing.

5.AI Assistant
  -Floating chatbot available on every page.
  -Can show help, contract summary, and system status.

#AI Chatbot (Frontend Assistant)

-Floating button at bottom-right of the screen
-Opens/closes smoothly
-Supports:
   -Help
   -Contract summary
   -System status

-Fully frontend-based (JavaScript)
-Clean separation of chatbot HTML, CSS, and JS



